headline: Disney, Universal, Warner Bros Discovery sue China's MiniMax for copyright infringement
summary: The suit, filed in the district court in California on Tuesday, claims MiniMax "audaciously" used the studios' famous copyrighted characters to market Hailuo as a "Hollywood studio in your pocket" and advertise and promote its service.  With a simple text prompt by a subscriber, Hailuo can generate downloadable images and videos of characters such as Darth Vader from "Star Wars", Minions from "Despicable Me" and "Wonder Woman" with MiniMax Hailuo branding, the lawsuit claims.  MiniMax failed to act on the studios' requests to take reasonable measures in place at several AI services to avoid infringement, according to the lawsuit.
